In this problem, Sam bought a total of 13 adventure books and 17 mystery books, so the number of books he bought in total is 13 + 17 = <<13+17=30>>30 books.
Out of these 30 books, 15 were used. So the number of new books Sam bought is 30 - 15 = <<30-15=15>>15 books. Therefore, Sam bought 15 new books. 
\boxed{15}

Adam started with 5 dollars. He then spent 2 dollars at the store. This means he now has 5 - 2 = 3 dollars.
After this, Adam receives an additional 5 dollars as his allowance. So he now has 3 + 5 = 8 dollars.
Therefore, Adam has 8 dollars now. \boxed{8}
